Internship provides students with practical experience in a newspaper, radio or television station. Internship consists of: 1) 4-week practical training in the press or electronic media 2) defence of one?s internship report at the seminar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop journalistic skills in different genres, introduce work in an editorial office along with the experience of analyzing the work of a journalist and editorial office.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the internship student
- is able to create a news story independently
- is able to discuss organizational and ethical dilemmas that occure in reporter's working process
- understands the work flow of journalistic organization
- has an overall understanding of newsroom's routines and demands set for published materials
- is able to to reflect critically upon own work
